HTML:HyperText MarkUp Language
-MarkUp Language
-Use html tags to create web elements
-h1 -h6 -> header
-p -> paragragh
-Opening tag : <h1>
-Closing tag : <h1/>
-Example : <h1> How are you? <h1/>

CSS: Cascade Style Sheet
Used for adding style such as color, width, height, spacing

There are 3 ways to add styling/ use CSS
-1. Inline : <h1 style= "color: red" > How are you? <h1/>
-2.Internal: Use style tag inside HTML file
<style>
h1{
    color: red;
}
<style/>
-3.External: Creating an external CSS Sheet.
In styles.css, we can use css files without using <style> keyword
       h1{
        color:red;
       }
       
Notes: External styling is preferred since it makes the code clean
       We should not use tags for styling. Class is the most common way to add styling for html
       Class is used for styling multiple elements .Class can repeat (. means class)
       Id is used for styling UNIQUE elements. Id should not repeat (# means id)